Package: MRDAG
Type: Package
Title: Mendelian Randomization for Directed Acyclic Graphs
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Minhao Yao
Maintainer: Minhao Yao <mhyaooo@nus.edu.sg>
Description: Implements a two-step algorithm for inferring causal graphs among proteins/genes using Mendelian Randomization. 
    First, it estimates a rough causal effects matrix using Two-stage Least Squares (2SLS) regressions by excluding cis-SNPs for target. 
    Second, it projects this matrix onto the space of Directed Acyclic Graphs (DAGs) using the NOTEARS continuous optimization constraint.
